.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Chinese+Archaeology&amp;rft.atitle=A+Survey+of+Gansang+site+and+Further+Discussion&amp;rft.date=2014-07-02&amp;rft.aulast=Xu&amp;rft.aufirst=Fengxian&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaogu.cn%2Fen%2FForum%2F2014%2F0702%2F46710.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASheldon+Gosline\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Nu-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Nu_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Nu, He (2014-07-02). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kaogu.cn/en/Forum/2014/0702/46706.html\">\"Thinking about the Sites in Pingguo county, S China\"</a>. <i>Chinese Archaeology</i>. Institute of Archaeology, Chinese Academy of Social Sciences<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">15 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Chinese+Archaeology&amp;rft.atitle=Thinking+about+the+Sites+in+Pingguo+county%2C+S+China&amp;rft.date=2014-07-02&amp;rft.aulast=Nu&amp;rft.aufirst=He&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaogu.cn%2Fen%2FForum%2F2014%2F0702%2F46706.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASheldon+Gosline\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/did-a-coded-message-lead-an-american-to-a-lost-civilization-in-china?ct=t(Newsletter_4_21_20164_20_2016)&amp;mc_cid=5e86c4b93a&amp;mc_eid=34be11d5e3\">[2]</a> Did A Coded Message Lead an American to a Lost Civilization in \nChina?  Sarah Laskow, <i>Atlas Obscura</i> (16 April 2016)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNew